726600f-a.title: Queens: Flushing Avenue - 53rd Street
726600f-a.text:
Flushing Ave., southside, weat of 53rd Street, showing in the
foreground the C.C. LFon house and Post Office of 1860. Some owners
were:Dominick Laube Vho sold to Feter Reiter who sold to Ernest Nurge.
Sheffield Dairy Company now occupies this site. The old numbers of
these houses were 1598 and 1602.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

727351f-a.title: Queens: Maspeth Avenue - 53rd Street
727351f-a.text:
Maspeth Ave., south side, between 53rd and 54th Streets, showing
the site upon which one stood the William H. Furman mansion. This
individual owned most of the surrounding land and homes in which many
members of his family lived.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
